deck_excerpt: Actually playing Crossout Designator as a combo piece
deck_description:
I don't know too much about what Kozmo can do, but I definitely know that it is very difficult to actually combine Kozmo and Prediction Princess together into a Deck, even if it is literally just 6 Kozmo cards. I understand that Kozmo has a gameplan where you are focusing on using your pilots to bring out your ships to gain advantage and reduce your opponent's available resources through your various interactions and interruptions. But that doesn't mix well with Prediction Princess, especially after their support. Prediction Princess focuses on getting to Prediction Princess Tarotrei and Prediction Princess Tarotreith in order to set up and build a board of Prediction Princess Ritual Monsters and Flip Monsters over the course of your turn and the start of your opponent's turn with your Flip Monsters either interrupting/stopping your opponent's plays while also netting you card advantage through searches with Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. With the completely opposite-facing ways to faciliate the set-up for both halves of the Deck it's a miracle that I even came up with a way to play Kozmo Prediction Princess. The Level 9 monster we are looking at today is Kozmo Dark Eclipser which is a Level 9 DARK Machine monster. Don't get your hopes up because we are literally incapable of ending on any Kozmo-related plays in our endboard because we just cannot fit the necessary cards to accomplish that in our Deck. We are just using Dark Eclipser and the Kozmo cards we are playing to put a Level 9 on board for World Legacy Monstrosity. I mean, the Deck is fine. It's not great, but it is really funny because we are actually using Crossout Designator as a combo piece in situations where we have access to it. You see, Kozmo Strawman can pay 500 Life Points to target a banished Kozmo monster and Special Summon it with its effect negated, destroying it during the End Phase. So, if we draw a way to get to Strawman, Crossout Designator, and World Legacy Monstrosity, we can Crossout calling Dark Eclipser and banish a copy of it from the Deck, Normal Summon Strawman and pay 500 to bring back the banished Dark Eclipser, and activate Monstrosity targeting Dark Eclipser to get Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler from Deck, giving you Rank 9 access for Mereologic Aggregator and Bibliomuse to faciliate your Prediction Princess plays. Again, the Deck is alright. It at least functions and you have a decent chance of opening full combo, whether it is purely just Prediction Princess plays or the Kozmo line to Dark Eclipser and then to your Prediction Princess. 

For the monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on the field face-up or face-down, and during the End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down. Tarotreith must be either Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect allows you to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from your GY if she was tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect can add a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand, and while she is face-up on the field, she gives your Ritual Monsters targeting and destruction protection from your opponent's effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 1 Trias Hierarchia to be sent off of the Diviners we are playing and it can Special Summon itself from hand or GY by tributing a Fairy monster. This basically can give you Rank 9 access, given you draw Diviner and Monstrosity as you can get Deus-X and Dark Eclipser off of Monstrosity targeting it on field. Speaking of, 2 Kozmo Dark Eclipser. This card cannot be targeted by your opponent's card effects and non-opt, during either player's turn, when a Trap Card is activated, you can banish a Kozmo from GY to negate the activation and destroy that card. And if it is destroyed by battle or card effect and sent to GY, you can banish it to add a Level 8 or lower Kozmo monster from Deck. This card is neat in Kozmo Decks, but we are just playing it as a Level 9. We are playing 2 because Crossout Designator only banishes from Deck and since it doesn't hurt if we draw 1 of them because Strawman, like all the Kozmo pilots, can banish themselves to Special Summon a ship from hand. 1 Kozmo Farmgirl which can banish itself during either player's turn to Special Summon a Level 4 or higher Kozmo monster from hand and if it inflicts battle damage to your opponent, you can pay 500 to search for a Kozmo card. I mean we are just playing Farmgirl as another pilot. I just felt like the Deck needed another pilot to potentially draw into, so Farmgirl is keeping Strawman company. And we are never using that second effect because it's gonna be pretty hard to inflict battle damage with 1500 ATK, and it's not like you can enter battle during turn 1 either way. 3 Kozmo Strawman who has the same first effect as Farmgirl, just Special Summoning Level 3 or higher Kozmo monsters from hand instead. And you can pay 500 Life Points once per turn to target and Special Summon a banished Kozmo monster with its effects negated, destroying it during the End Phase. 3 Diviner of the Herald which sends a Fairy monster from Deck or Extra Deck to GY on Normal or Special Summon to increase its Level by the Level of the sent monster which you are using to send either Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck or Trias Hierarchia from Deck. And finally, 2 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring as potential handtraps, but mainly to add more use to our Crossouts. 

Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 Emergency Teleport which gets us any of our Kozmo pilots from Deck. 3 Crossout Designator which allows you to declare a card name and banish that declared card from your Main Deck to negate its effects and the activated effect and effects on field of cards with the same original name. Usually, you are using this against handtraps, but we are using it to banish Dark Eclipser, and not being able to activate its effects doesn't matter at all as we are never using them either way. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess from Deck face-down. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which can either Special Summon a Level 9 from hand or target a Level 9 you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than that monster, but with different names. And finally, 3 Infinite Impermanence. We are not playing Gold Sarcophagus because it's only at 1, meaning that we have a large chance of not drawing it, and while it does also banish a monster from Deck, leaving a potential Crossout in hand to deal with a potential handtrap, I just find it not very good as Crossout. Crossout can banish a card from Deck and can protect you, both being in different applications and situations of course, but drawing Gold Sarc when you have full Prediction Princess combo without the use of your Kozmo cards, leaves it sitting there all stupid. Crossout just feels better to play and has more usage overall, especially when you don't have access to the Kozmo part of your Deck. Sure, it might give you another way to banish a monster from Deck, but it's not "that" good to consider also playing it. 

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches for a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 1 Super Starslayer TY-PHON - Sky Crisis. 1 Infinitrack Earth Slicer. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Nine-Lives Cat. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows, and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Underworld Goddess of the Closed World, 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 2 Droll & Lock Bird, 2 Triple Tactics Talent, 2 Lightning Storm, 3 Dark Ruler No More, and 3 Evenly Matched.

deck_excerpt: Combining both Jake Stox's list and any hand loop list, here is Modern VW Handloop V1.0
deck_description:
Inspired by a Virtual World list by Norwich Regional 5th placer Jake Stox and other VW hand loop lists, the goal with this list is simple: try to make a very consistent hand loop "FTK."

There are a couple of cards that I'm considering putting in: Overdrive Teleporter, more copies of Wheeleler and Tracker, and Trishula (especially since Tear is a deck that exists and in the case that I'm going second I'm going to need to get rid of some cards on board).

There are a few glaring problems with the deck that I intend to fix:

  1. Quem is in the format.
  2. This is a going-first deck.
  3. Beast of the Pharaoh is a Zombie, not a psychic.

deck_name: Beginner's Guide to Infernoble (feat. Pak's YCS List)
deck_excerpt: Combining DUNE with AGOVE support, Infernoble has consistently become a top finisher in YCS!
deck_description:
Combining Duelist Nexus with Age of Overlord support, Infernoble has consistently become a top finisher in YCS! A new win condition under the form of Emperor Charles the Great, consistency boosters comparable to Isolde being Angelica - Princess of Noble Arms, busted S/T negation with Angelic Ring (negates stuff like Dark Ruler and Super Poly), and extra starters with the Sinful Spoils package! This increase of power and consistency comes with the ability to stuff the deck with a ton of staples while still being playable - enabling a fearsome combo deck with power to rival the historical figure Charles the Great!

 

It seems that Infernoble has gained a new powerful identify when compared to it's hand-looping, generic boss monster turboing predecessor back with its release with Rise of the Duelist at 2020. The recent support for this deck has once again reached critical mass for competitive play, enabling Infernoble to play as a top meta contender. The boards this deck generates are unique, interesting and ridiculously powerful! 

 

The decklist in this guide inspired by Pak's top YCS Richmond and YCS Bologna finish with Infernoble. He explains everything in-depth, his theorycrafting and combos with his Youtube video much better than I can with this written article. Be sure to check it out!

 

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

 
ARCHETYPES AND DECKBUILDING
 
The structure of the standard INFERNOBLE deck changes dramatically after Age of Overlord. The Infernoble core is very compact since every combo piece is highly searchable (via Isolde, Museum and Sinful Spoils), allowing the maindeck knights to be 1-ofs. The Noble Knight starters are 3-ofs with Arms Museum also searchable with Terraforming. 3 Heritage of the Chalice searches for any Noble Knight monster or Noble Arms. Finally, 1 ROTA gets any warrior monster. 
 
Age of Overlord also brings the SINFUL SPOILS engine to Infernoble, allowing for another layer of consistency. The Sinful Spoils package is primarily used for WANTED: Seeker to search for Diabellstar, so she can set Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye from deck. Snake-Eye summons from deck a level 1 Fire monster, that being either Infernoble Knight Renaud or Fire Flint Lady. All of this does not use up your valuable normal summon allowing for an easier way to get to Isolde! Finally, WANTED: Seeker recycles Original Sinful Spoils for a 1 card draw. 
 
There are 6 EQUIP spells in this deck, and they are mostly garnets to be sent to the GY via Isolde. During the End Phase, these equips (usually Angelic Ring) is equipped to Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. You may not want to draw into these garnets, but Infernoble Arms - Durendal is fine to draw into (hence it's a 2-of) since it searches for a level 5 or lower Fire Warrior from deck. 
 
Finally, there are 12 STAPLE slots in this deck. These staples can be exchanged with the Side Deck! 
 
COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN
 
Infernoble's gameplan is to create a unbreakable board that your opponent simply cannot hope to play through. It generally ends on 2-3 spell/trap negates, 1 quick effect pop, and 1 monster negate/destroy. If there are extenders, the board can also have Baronne, S:P Little Knight and Apollousa. 

There are multiple pathways to respectable Infernoble boards that all vary in power depending on how many times you've been interrupted and whatever cards you have in your hand. However, they all centre around resolving both of Isolde's effects. If Isolde is interrupted, the backup plan is to summon S:P Little Knight. 
 
The 12 handtraps maindecked should hopefully be enough to simplify the gamestate so that S:P can control your opponent until you can full combo with Isolde. 
 
Here is the Infernoble 1-card combo:
 
Neo-Space Connector = Emperor Charles the Great (Pop 1 card, spell/trap negate destroy) + Angelica's Angel Ring (Spell speed 4 mandatory spell negate) + Phoenix Gearfried (monster negate destroy) + S:P Little Knight (target monster banish) + Angelica (If targeted, GY set-up and banishes herself until end phase) + potential hand rip and hand knowledge (Aqua Dolphin's optional effect) + draw 1
  1. Normal summon Connector.  Activate Connector's on-summon effect to summon Aqua Dolphin from deck. 
  2. Activate Aqua Dolphin's effect to look at your opponent's hand and hand-rip a card from it (if applicable, and sniping their droll/ash is optimal). 
  3. Link summon Isolde using Connector + Aqua Dolphin. 
  4. Activate Isolde's on-summon effect to search for Fire Flint Lady. 
  5. Activate Isolde's effect sending Phoenix Blade, Angelica's Angelic Ring, D.D.R. - Different Dimension Reincarnation and Infernoble Arms - Durendal to summon Infernoble Knight Ogier from deck. 
  6. Activate Ogier's on-summon effect to send Infernoble Knight Turpin from deck to GY. 
  7. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Connector and Aqua Dolphin. 
  8. Equip Ogier with Phoenix Blade. 
  9. Activate Turpin's effect from the GY to summon itself since you control a monster equipped with a card. 
  10. XYZ summon Battlin' Boxer King Dempsey using Ogier + Turpin. Activate Dempsey's on-summon effect to search for Infernoble Knight Renaud from deck. 
  11. Special summon Renaud. Activate Renaud's on-summon effect to recover Different Dimension Reincarnation from GY to hand. 
  12. Activate Different Dimension Reincarnation discarding Fire Flint Lady to summon from banished pile Connector. 
  13. Synchro summon Anglica, Princess of Noble Arms using Renaud + Connector. Activate Angelica's on-summon effect to search for Noble Arms Museum. 
  14. Activate Noble Arms Museum. Activate Museum's effect paying 1200 LP to search for Infernoble Arms - Almace. 
  15. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Connector and Fire Flint Lady. 
  16. CL2 equip Anglica with Phoenix Blade and CL2 activate Angelica's effect to send Pheonix Gearfried to the to GY, banish herself and summon from Extra Deck Infernoble Knight Roland.
  17. Activate Dempsey's effect by detaching Turpin. 
  18. Activate Turpin's effect, equiping him to Infernoble Knight Roland. 
  19. Activate Noble Arms Museum's effect to special summon Turpin from the backrow. 
  20. Synchro Summon Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles using Turpin + Roland. 
  21. Equip Almace to Emperor Charles. 
  22. Link summon Emperor Charles the Great using Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. 
  23. CL1 Emperor Charles the Great's effect to target equip Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles in the GY, CL2 Almace's effect to target and add back to hand Phoenix Gearfried from GY.
  24. Link summon S:P Little Knight using Isolde + Dempsey. 
  25. Special summon Phoenix Gearfried by banishing Infernoble Arms - Durendal from GY.
  26. Activate Ogier's effect in the GY to equip itself to Emperor Charles the Great. 
  27. During the endphase, Angelica summons herself back to the field. 
  28. During the endphase, Emperor Charles the Great activates his effect (these effects were obtained from the equipped Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles) to equip Angelica's Angelic Ring from the GY and Infernoble Knight Maugis. 
  29. Emperor Charles the Great's trigger effect activates, destroying Maugis. 
  30. Maugis' trigger effect activates, shuffling back to deck from banished pile Infernoble Arms - Durendal, Infernoble Arms - Almace and Fire Flint Lady to draw 1 card. 
  31. During your opponent's main phase, you can equip Infernoble Knight Roland to Emperor Charles the Great to trigger his destruction effect. 
From merely 1 card, the Infernoble player has summoned an army of monsters with more interactions than the opponent has cards in their hand (especially if you hand-ripped earlier)! This uninterrupted 1 card combo is currently unparallelled in this age of modern Yugioh - it's so ridiculously strong, which is befitting a deck based on Charles the Great. But hold on, this gets better with the Sinful Spoils engine!   
 
Diabellestarr + Any fire warrior + 1 discard = Emperor Charles the Great (Pop 1 card, spell/trap negate destroy) + Angelica's Angel Ring (Spell speed 4 mandatory spell negate) + Phoenix Gearfried (monster negate destroy) + 3 material Apollousa (3 monster negates) + Angelica (If targeted, GY set-up and banishes herself until end phase) + potential hand rip and hand knowledge (Aqua Dolphin's optional effect) + draw 1
  1. Normal summon fire warrior. 
  2. Special summon Diabellestar by discarding 1 card. Activate Diabellestar's on-summon effect setting from deck Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye. 
  3. Activate Original Sinful Spoils by sending Diabellestar to the GY to summon from deck Infernoble Knight Ricciardetto. 
  4. Link summon Isolde using fire warrior + Ricciardetto. 
  5. Activate Isolde's on-summon effect to search for Connector. 
  6. Activate Isolde's effect sending Phoenix Blade, Angelica's Angelic Ring, D.D.R. - Different Dimension Reincarnation and Infernoble Arms - Durendal to summon Infernoble Knight Ogier from deck. 
  7. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Ricciardetto and fire warrior. 
  8. Equip Ogier with Phoenix Blade. 
  9. Activate Turpin's effect from the GY to summon itself since you control a monster equipped with a card. 
  10. XYZ summon Battlin' Boxer King Dempsey using Ogier + Turpin. Activate Dempsey's on-summon effect to search for Infernoble Knight Renaud from deck. 
  11. Special summon Renaud. Activate Renaud's on-summon effect to recover Different Dimension Reincarnation from GY to hand.
  12. Link summon a 2400ATK Apollousa using Isolde + Renaud + Dempsey.
  13. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Isolde and Dempsey.
  14. Activate Different Dimension Reincarnation discarding Phoenix Blade to summon from banished pile Ricciardetto.
  15. Activate Ricciardetto's on-summon effect to summon from GY Turpin. 
  16. Synchro summon Anglica, Princess of Noble Arms using Ricciardetto + Turpin. Activate Angelica's on-summon effect to search for Noble Arms Museum. 
  17. Activate Noble Arms Museum. Activate Museum's effect paying 1200 LP to search for Infernoble Arms - Almace. 
  18. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Ricciardetto and Renaud. 
  19. CL2 equip Anglica with Phoenix Blade and CL2 activate Angelica's effect to send Pheonix Gearfried to the to GY, banish herself and summon from Extra Deck Infernoble Knight Roland.
  20. Equip Roland with Infernoble Arms - Almace. 
  21. Activate Turpin's effect, equiping him to Infernoble Knight Roland. 
  22. Activate Noble Arms Museum's effect to special summon Turpin from the backrow. 
  23. Synchro Summon Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles using Turpin + Roland. 
  24. Activate Almace's effect to target and add back to hand Phoenix Gearfried from GY.
  25. Activate Roland's effect in the GY to equip himself to Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. 
  26. Link summon Emperor Charles the Great using Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. 
  27. Activate Emperor Charles the Great's on-summon effect to target equip Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles in the GY.
  28. Activate Ogier's effect in the GY to equip itself to Emperor Charles the Great. 
  29. Special summon Phoenix Gearfried by banishing Infernoble Arms - Durendal from GY.
  30. During the endphase, Angelica summons herself back to the field. 
  31. During the endphase, Emperor Charles the Great activates his effect (these effects were obtained from the equipped Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles) to equip Angelica's Angelic Ring from the GY and Infernoble Knight Maugis. 
  32. Emperor Charles the Great's trigger effect activates, destroying Maugis. 
  33. Maugis' trigger effect activates, shuffling back to deck from banished pile Infernoble Arms - Durendal, Infernoble Arms - Almace and fire warrior to draw 1 card. 
  34. During your opponent's main phase, you can equip Infernoble Knight Roland to Emperor Charles the Great to trigger his destruction effect.
GENERAL TIPS
  • Being a combo deck, Infernoble functions like Mannadium, Dragonlink and Cyberse Mathmech. They can all create scary boards, but kind of suck going 2nd. The 12 handtraps coupled with the amount of gas Infernoble has theoretically should enable this deck to simplify the gamestate, play through interruption and full combo, but if you know for sure you can't make it through what your opponent has, just go to next game. It's better that you take the loss and not give your opponent any information so they don't side the right cards against this strategy. 
  • The backup for this strategy if you can't resolve Isolde is S:P Little Knight! You can even link away S:P Little Knight to make Isolde the following turn when it's safer to do so. That's why there are two S:Ps in the Extra Deck (ouch that's expensive for IRL decks lol). 
  • You can make Baronne before Isolde with Diabellestarr + Ash Blossom. Baronne can also be made with Infernoble Knight Charles + a level 1 tuner like Ricardetto or Renaud. 
  • Noble Arms Musuem is a soft once per turn. Multiple Museums means you can summon up to two Emperor Charles the Great! Be sure to not link off Isolde for S:P until you have both Charles on field, since you need Isolde's link zones to summon two of them. 
  • If you have a garnet you wanted to search in your opening hand, try to get the card in the GY somehow (either by using it, discarding it for Neo Aqua Dolphin or Different Dimension Reincarnation's effect). Then you get Infernoble Knight Maugis in the GY to shuffle it back so you can properly search the garnet later in your combo. 
  • In games 2 and 3, side in Called By the Grave with Crossout Designator since your opponent is also siding in handtraps (like the fearsome Droll) to hardcounter your strategy. 
  • Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
CONCLUDING REMARKS
 
As a history nerd, the chance to field Charles the Great is like a dream come true! And he really does live up to his "The Great" title, since this boss monster (coupled with his bestie S:P Little Knight) is enough to boost this strategy to meta relevance once again! The consistency that the Diabellestarr engine and the new Infernoble cards of Museum and Angelica really push the deck to the next level of power since it allows so much staple cards to be used with the deck like the 12 handtraps. Perhaps now Charles the Great can be revered and respected as much as his historical counterpart in our favourite children's card game Yugioh. As this deck's pilot, can you live up to the greatness of his name?
 
GLHF Duelists!

Not really sure how viable this deck is but I thought it would be fun to make a deck out of a seemilgly weak card/archetype. There has been a ton of support for these cards so even though they look cute, best to tread carefully!

deck_excerpt: Making use of Over Future Fusion
deck_description:
The Level 9 monster we are looking at today is Chimeratech Overdragon which is a Level 9 DARK Machine Fusion Monster that requires Cyber Dragon and 1 or more Machine monsters as Fusion Material. Look, I know that we are focusing on trying to Summon Overdragon in this Deck, so a Cyber Dragon Prediction Princess Deck is a possibility. However, it would never come into fruition. There are 2 reasons for this. First of all, all of the good Cyber Dragon cards and Cyber Spell/Traps Machine-lock you. This is a bit of a stretch but cards like Cybernetic Horizon, Cyber Dragon Nachster, and Cyber Dragon Herz all have good effects for either Cyber Dragon plays or are able to really turbo your way to Overdragon, but they Machine-lock you. I'm not saying that they are particularly good (in the case of Cybernetic Horizon in the bricks you need to play) or what you would theoretically play in a Cyber Dragon Prediction Princess Deck, but I would've liked to experiment with it as a Deck at the very least, either having like a Cyber Dragon Infinity (or idk Cybernetic Overflow?) as a part of my endboard or having the ability to go into a Chimeratech Rampage Dragon on my following turn for a Quick OTK. Second, have you read what Overdragon does? It sends your entire board other than itself to the GY on Fusion Summon. Even if you were able to make some assemblance of a Cyber Dragon board before going into your Prediction Princess plays, Overdragon just throws it all into the GY when its Summoned as a mandatory effect. And so I have ended up with this Deck that intends on turboing out Overdragon for a Level 9 on field for World Legacy Monstrosity, and to be fair, it's probably better than what Cyber Dragon Prediction Princess would've been. We are utilizing Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio and Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra to search for the current OCG-exclusive Over Future Fusion. I mean if this card doesn't scream "Make Chimeratech Overdragon", I don't know what does (probably Cybernetic Horizon actually). It reads that you can activate each of its effects once per turn. You can reveal a Fusion Monster in your Extra Deck and send a named Fusion Material monster from your Deck to GY, but you cannot Special Summon monsters with that name nor activate their monster effects this turn. And you can also Fusion Summon a DARK Machine Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck by banishing materials from your GY. This means that we can make Overdragon and go through our whole Prediction Princess line through a 2.5 card combo of Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, World Legacy Monstrosity, and a monster to discard for Scorpio. Normal Summon Scorpio and discard a monster to Special Summon Cobra from Deck. Cobra searches for Over Future Fusion. Activate Over Future Fusion and use its first effect to dump Cyber Dragon from Deck. Link off Cobra and Scorpio into Sky Striker Ace - Camellia which is a generic Link-2 Machine monster. Then we Link off Camellia for any Sky Striker Link-1, I am playing Sky Striker Ace - Kagari. This gets Camellia into GY, giving you Cydra and a Machine in GY, so now you can activate Over Future Fusion's second effect to banish Cydra and Camellia to Fusion Summon Overdragon. Overdragon sends the rest of your field to the GY, and now you activate Monstrosity targeting Overdragon for Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler and you should know the rest. I mean, the Deck is cool, but I'd much rather be playing a more interesting Prediction Princess variant that actually has the ability to produce more of a unique endboard. 

For the monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on the field face-up or face-down, and during the End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down. Tarotreith must be either Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect allows you to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from your GY if she was tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect can add a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand, and while she is face-up on the field, she gives your Ritual Monsters targeting and destruction protection from your opponent's effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 1 Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light which can be Summoned off of the Lonefire Blossoms we are playing for a Level 9 and on Normal or Special Summon, it can search a Generaider card or a Plant monster. She also works as a nice Small World bridge from Diviner to her to a Predaplant or Lonefire. 2 Cyber Dragon. You realistically only need 1, but Over Future Fusion only does send from Deck. Even if you draw 1 copy, you can still use it as a Small World bridge from it to Mardel to Diviner or a Predaplant or Lonefire. 3 Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio which sends a monster from hand or GY on Normal or Special Summon to Special Summon a Predaplant from Deck. 1 Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra which adds a Fusion of Polymerization Spell card from your Deck to your hand once per Duel if it is Special Summoned by the effect of a Predaplant monster. 2 Lonefire Blossom which can Tribute a Plant to Special Summon a Plant from Deck. 3 Diviner of the Herald which sends a Fairy from Deck or Extra Deck to GY to increase its Level by the Level of the sent monster. It's good for Small World bridging and you can just Normal Summon it to send Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck for a Ritual search to go through your Ritual plays from there. And finally, 3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring. 

For Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Over Future Fusion. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down, and you can also banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which Special Summons a Level 9 from hand or targets a Level 9 you control and Special Summons 2 Level 9's from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than that monster, but with different names. And finally, 3 Small World. 

Extra Deck: 1 Chimeratech Overdragon, 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon, and 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck if sent to GY. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess and 1 Cross-Sheep to get more use out of Scorpio and Cobra through searching for Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 1 S:P Little Knight and 1 I:P Masquerena. 1 Sky Striker Ace - Camellia and 1 Sky Striker Ace - Kagari. Camellia is just a generic Link-2 Machine that we can easily Link off since all of the Sky Striker Link-1's just need a Sky Striker monster that isn't their Attribute as material. This gets you a Machine into GY for Over Future Fusion to get you Overdragon. I am choosing to play Kagari, and while you can send a Sky Striker Spell from Deck to GY with Camellia and add it back to hand upon Link Summoning Kagari, there is never going to be a moment where we don't have a monster in our Main Monster Zones, meaning that we can't make use of any of the Sky Striker Spells, even if we wanted to. But you could play any Sky Striker Link-1 that you fancy. Finally, 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Dark Ruler No More, 2 Triple Tactics Thrust, 1 Triple Tactics Talent, 2 Infinite Impermanence, and 3 Evenly Matched.

Hi, it's my first try to a somewhat competitive deck since i went back to play YGO.
This deck wants to keep many options of negation effects when not starting first and eventually bring out Iris as a double-down on an impermanence.
On first turn, the branded strategy goes well in parallel with the swordsoul. Discarding cards with Longyuan helps to add fuel for a Branded in White fusion and Swordsoul synchros can be used to bring out Icejade if needed. Branded in High spirit synergizes well with the Swordsoul, as putting one and Icejade can let Taia do its thing. Lastly, Ecclesia is an all-around all star in this strategy, fueling both paths and easily coming back in one's hand

deck_name: SPOILS of conquest- my Ariseheart x Diabellstar fanfic deck
deck_excerpt: Firery flames engulf wraithsoth as a new deck is born!
deck_description: a quaint deck i made usng my spoils (heh) of using the pack simulator (do not build it is very expensive)

ok so this idea wasn't mine but i built the deck from scratch, trying to optimize it as much as possible. The vanilla vaalmonica combo is
Dimonno Vaalmonica or Angello Vaalmonica -> Vaalmonica Scelta -> Vaalmonica, the Agathokakological Voice -> another Dimonno -> pendulum summon Dimonno -> copy Scelta to grab Vaalmonica Versare -> ditch a trap card, you could choose between Vaalmonica Followed Rhythm or Vaalmonica Chosen Melody (i use followed). The only problem of this combo is that it totally ignores the aromages and makes you start with -2000 lp

the aromage combo is One for One  / Lonefire Blossom  / other shenanigans to summon Aromalylith Rosalina -> Aromage Laurel -> Aromaseraphy Jasmine -> Therion "Lily" Borea -> Therion Discolosseum -> Cattycorn if you have no cards on the field, to grab the vaalmonica field spell and autopilot vaalmonicas before continuing the combo, or Aromaseraphy Angelica to extend it with a synchro summon -> Aromalylith Rosemary to grab Aroma Blend , discard Discolosseum and set Humid Winds , then fusion summon Aromalylith Magnolia / activate angelica and other "if you have more lp" effects, activate ONLY the first effect of Humid winds to grab Aromage Marjoram , activate the second effect to special summon it using rosemary, synchro summon Aromaseraphy Sweet Marjoram with marjoram and angelica or other shenanigans, grab Blessed Winds and set it. If you did everything correctly, you should end up with a standard aromage board, + two pendulum vaalmonicas with x2/3 counters on angel

in the side deck cactus bouncer is used as a start first special summon negate, even if you'll develop a weaker board. Child's play can be replaced with evenly matched, but it works well with the rest of the deck and it's fun if the opponent can't read
